	<key>readme</key>
	<string>Save clipboard text to a .txt file with one keystroke.

## Usage

  save              → ~/Downloads/quick_save_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.txt
  save notes        → ~/Downloads/notes.txt
  save notes.md     → ~/Downloads/notes.md

Copy text to your clipboard, type "save" in Alfred, and press Enter.
If a file with the same name already exists, (1), (2), … is appended automatically.

## Configuration

Open "Configure Workflow" to set the save directory (default: ~/Downloads).

## Requirements

Python 3.9+</string>
